rows.title: Welcome to Parenting for Respectibility
rows.goal_1: Introductions, explore expectations, set ground rules and discuss roles of the facilitator.
To appreciate the importance of family relationships especially relations with one’s children and partner.
rows.goal_2: To encourage participants to recruit their partners.
rows.title: @data.topic.family_relation.title

rows.goal_1: To explore parents’ current beliefs and practices regarding parent – child interaction.
rows.goal_2: To discuss parenting goals and factors that facilitate the achievement of the goals.
rows.title: @data.topic.current_pract.title

rows.goal_1: To explore the basic developmental needs and behaviors of children 0 – 17 years.
rows.goal_2: To discuss the importance of fathers’ supportiveness during pregnancy and childhood.
rows.goal_3: To show how parenting practices are important for children to reach their full potential.
rows.title: @data.topic.child_dev.title

rows.goal_1: To reflect on the influence of parent figures on participants while they were growing up.
rows.goal_2: To discuss how participants can build on their parents’ positive influences, and avoid repeating their negative influences.
rows.goal_3: To identify and learn new ways to encourage good behavior without being violent.
rows.title: @data.topic.parent_childhood.title

rows.goal_1: To discuss positive parent-child interaction to improve discipline and respectability in families.
rows.goal_2: To explore different styles of parenting and demonstrate sensitive parenting that which promotes positive relationships and respectability.
rows.title: @data.topic.positive_parenting.title

rows.goal_1: To reflect upon how gender norms can be harmful to both women and men, girls and boys. (check harriet)
rows.goal_2: To increase the awareness of gendered power differences within families.
rows.goal_3: To encourage men to commit to positive notions of ‘being a man’.
rows.title: @data.topic.gender_power.title

rows.goal_1: To reflect on own experiences and common causes of spousal conflict.
rows.goal_2: To discuss the effects of spousal conflict on parenting.
rows.title: @data.topic.impact_conflict.title

rows.goal_1: To reflect on the time men and women dedicate to caring for their children and shaping their future.
rows.goal_2: To identify how men and women can be more involved in family life.
rows.title: @data.topic.sharing_care.title

rows.goal_1: To learn how excessive drinking affects relationships and children.
rows.goal_2: To learn how to help a partner to reduce alcohol consumption and other socially unacceptable practices.
rows.goal_3: To discuss what constitutes a healthy marriage and sexuality.
rows.title: @data.topic.healthy_relation.title
Review
rows.goal_1: To reflect on all single sex sessions and plan for the mixed sex sessions.
To identify the differences between punishment and discipline.
rows.goal_2: To explore the effects of punishment on children’s development. To practice effective strategies of managing anger and disappointment.
rows.goal_3: To discuss how to positively and sensitively engage with children to promote respect.
rows.title: @data.topic.discipline.title

rows.goal_1: To increase parents’ engagement at school and cooperation with teachers.
rows.goal_2: To learn how to encourage children to achieve through education.
rows.title: @data.topic.education.title

rows.goal_1: To understand how gender expectations affect the lives of women and men, and of girls and boys.
rows.goal_2: To discuss strategies to modify discriminatory gender norms.
rows.goal_3: To reflect upon communication and affection between parents and sons and how this affects their well being.
rows.title: @data.topic.gender_equality.title

rows.goal_1: To discuss constructive ways of sharing information to avoid violent situation in relationships. Express personal needs and feelings and listen reflectively and empathically.
rows.title: @data.topic.abuse_prevention.title

rows.goal_1: To reflect on the participants’ experience of the programme
rows.goal_2: To reinforce commitment to positive more equitable and respectful parenting
rows.goal_3: To encourage continued meetings after the programme formally ends.
rows.title: @data.topic.reduce_conflict.title
